description:
Real-time DDoS detection from simulated Cisco ASA firewall logs. Generates background traffic and a controllable attack stream, parses raw syslog into structured fields, then applies dynamic per-IP baselines (overall and hourly) to detect traffic spikes. Fires a webhook alert when the spike ratio exceeds the configured threshold. Resume and pause the attack MV to control the simulation.
The attack MV is paused automatically on install. To trigger the simulated attack:
  SYSTEM RESUME MATERIALIZED VIEW <db>.mv_asa_logs_sim_attack;
